# FVM Usage Guide

This project uses FVM (Flutter Version Management) for consistent Flutter SDK versioning. All Flutter commands should be prefixed with `fvm`.

## Key Files
- [.fvmrc](mdc:.fvmrc) - Contains the Flutter version configuration
- [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml) - Project dependencies and configuration

## Command Usage

Always use the `fvm` prefix for Flutter commands:

✅ Correct:
```bash
fvm flutter pub get
fvm flutter build web
fvm flutter run
fvm flutter gen-l10n
```

❌ Incorrect:
```bash
flutter pub get
flutter build web
flutter run
flutter gen-l10n
```

This ensures consistent Flutter SDK version usage across the team and prevents version mismatches.
